      "description": "Offering a museum-grade 2004 BMW M3 (E46) featuring the legendary S54 3.2L inline-six. This high-revving masterpiece utilizes individual throttle bodies and double-VANOS to deliver 333hp with a razor-sharp 8,000 RPM redline. The drivetrain is anchored by a precise Getrag 6-speed manual gearbox and a variable M-differential lock for superior power delivery. This example is mechanically flawless, having received comprehensive preventative maintenance including rear subframe reinforcement and a full VANOS overhaul. The chassis remains exceptionally rigid, supported by a meticulously preserved suspension geometry that retains factory-spec damping and compliance. The exterior finish is concours-ready with no evidence of road rash or oxidation, while the cabin maintains its original tactile integrity with no bolster wear. A true turn-key specimen for the discerning purist.",
